-- South Africa Leads 10-Man France 2-0 After 60 Minutes of World Cup Match
-- Bob Bensch
-- 2010-06-22T15:20:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/south-africa-leads-10-man-france-2-0-after-60-minutes-of-world-cup-match.html

          
          
             South Africa leads 10-man France 2-0
after 60 minutes of their final World Cup Group A game in
Bloemfontein.  
 Bongami Khumalo and Katlego Mphela have scored for South
Africa. Franceâ€™s Yoann Gourcuff received a red card in the 25th
minute for elbowing MacBeth Shibaya as they jumped for the ball.  
 Uruguay leads Mexico 1-0 in the second half of the other
Group A game in Rustenburg. Both teams have four points and will
qualify for the round of 16 with a tie. France and South Africa
have one point each. The top two teams in each group advance.  
          
          


  


        